This article is about a speech delivered by President Obama at Nellis Air Force Base. The speech focused on the progress made in the first 100 days of the Recovery Act and the efforts to rebuild America's economy. The audience consisted of airmen, base workers, and their families. Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid introduced the President. Several elected officials were also expected to attend the speech. The article also provided information on the amount of Recovery Act funding allocated to Nevada, including funds for Social Security stimulus payments, Medicaid assistance, highway planning and construction, and grants for education.